      public static Locale getSystemsLocale()
      Returns the system's Locale (as determined by the JVM at startup, Locale.getDefault()). Should be used to show locale dependent information in the system's locale.

      Note: The default locale is overridden with the ZAP's user defined locale/language.

      Returns:
      the system's Locale
      See Also:
      • Locale.setDefault(Locale)

      public static boolean isDevMode()
      Tells whether or not the "dev mode" should be enabled.

      Should be used to enable development related utilities/functionalities.

      Returns:
      true if the "dev mode" should be enabled, false otherwise.
      Since:
      2.8.0

    • setDevMode

      public static void setDevMode(boolean devMode)
      Sets whether or not the "dev mode" should be enabled.

      Note: This method should be called only by bootstrap classes.

      Parameters:

    • setSilent

      public static void setSilent(boolean silent)
      Sets whether or not ZAP should be 'silent' i.e. not make any unsolicited requests.

      Note: This method should be called only by bootstrap classes.

      Parameters:
      silent - true if ZAP should be silent, false otherwise.
      Since:
      2.8.0
